messages.content: ComfyUI_rotate_image is a custom node designed to rotate images using the Img2Img process.
What type of functionality does this custom node provide?
This custom node provides the ability to rotate images by leveraging the Img2Img process.
Does the ComfyUI_rotate_image node use the Img2Img node to provide its functionality?
Yes, the ComfyUI_rotate_image node uses the Img2Img node to enable image rotation.
What is the underlying process used in the ComfyUI_rotate_image node?
The underlying process used in the ComfyUI_rotate_image node is the Img2Img process.
How can I use the ComfyUI_rotate_image node?

To use the ComfyUI_rotate_image node, you will need to incorporate it into your ComfyUI workflow, which typically involves connecting it with other nodes in the GUI to rotate images as desired using the Img2Img process.
